.TH "snd_hda_codec_amp_init" 9 "snd_hda_codec_amp_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_hda_codec_amp_init \- initialize the AMP value
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_hda_codec_amp_init
.BI "(struct hda_codec *codec "  ","
.BI "hda_nid_t nid "  ","
.BI "int ch "  ","
.BI "int dir "  ","
.BI "int idx "  ","
.BI "int mask "  ","
.BI "int val "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "codec" 12
the HDA codec
.IP "nid" 12
NID to read the AMP value
.IP "ch" 12
channel (left=0 or right=1)
.IP "dir" 12
#HDA_INPUT or #HDA_OUTPUT
.IP "idx" 12
the index value (only for input direction)
.IP "mask" 12
bit mask to set
.IP "val" 12
the bits value to set
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Works like \fBsnd_hda_codec_amp_update\fP but it writes the value only at
the first access.  If the amp was already initialized / updated beforehand,
this does nothing.
